WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:middle
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:12.940 --> 00:00:14.670
Inherited will...

3
00:00:14.670 --> 00:00:17.580
the tides of time, and humanity's dreams...

4
00:00:17.580 --> 00:00:20.410
They cannot be stopped.

5
00:00:20.410 --> 00:00:23.520
As long as people seek freedom,

6
00:00:23.520 --> 00:00:26.150
these things will never cease to be.

7
00:00:34.860 --> 00:00:41.080
I only believe in the future -- I don't care if anyone laughs

8
00:00:41.120 --> 00:00:46.600
That racing passion makes you shine

9
00:00:46.620 --> 00:00:52.140
It's too bright, but I want to gaze at it

10
00:00:52.480 --> 00:00:56.120
I sense "aesthetics" somewhere

11
00:00:59.480 --> 00:01:02.740
I follow, follow in the footsteps

12
00:01:02.740 --> 00:01:06.030
of a dream that resembles no one

13
00:01:06.030 --> 00:01:09.260
Until I dramatically get it

14
00:01:18.120 --> 00:01:21.160
I'm going to catch, catch the shape

15
00:01:21.260 --> 00:01:24.240
of a dream no one can see

16
00:01:24.520 --> 00:01:30.260
I'm going to go with you, so passionate feelings

17
00:01:30.500 --> 00:01:33.620
I don't really need everything to add up

18
00:01:33.600 --> 00:01:36.790
Rather than run-of-the-mill daily life,

19
00:01:36.800 --> 00:01:40.390
run for paradise instead

20
00:01:49.960 --> 00:01:54.430
<b>Cape Promise</b>

21
00:02:06.860 --> 00:02:08.320
It's a flower!

22
00:02:07.570 --> 00:02:08.320
A flower?

23
00:02:13.280 --> 00:02:15.280
Oh, never mind. It's a person.

24
00:02:15.280 --> 00:02:16.570
What is he?

25
00:02:16.570 --> 00:02:20.120
That old guy killed an imperial
squid in one fell swoop...

26
00:02:20.120 --> 00:02:21.870
Was he just fishing...

27
00:02:21.870 --> 00:02:24.960
or was he trying to save us...?

28
00:02:52.240 --> 00:02:54.700
Say something already, jerk!

29
00:02:57.660 --> 00:03:00.200
I-If you wanna fight,
we'll fight, you bastard!

30
00:03:00.200 --> 00:03:01.910
We've got cannons!

31
00:03:09.000 --> 00:03:11.880
You'd better stop what you're
doing before someone dies.

32
00:03:15.220 --> 00:03:16.510
Oh, yeah?

33
00:03:16.510 --> 00:03:17.760
And just who's gonna die?

34
00:03:17.760 --> 00:03:18.970
Me.

35
00:03:18.970 --> 00:03:20.220
You?!

36
00:03:20.220 --> 00:03:21.010
You damn...

37
00:03:21.010 --> 00:03:22.060
Hey, calm down.

38
00:03:22.060 --> 00:03:24.480
That bastard's mocking us...

39
00:03:25.770 --> 00:03:27.770
Hey, gramps!

40
00:03:27.770 --> 00:03:30.650
How about you tell us
who you are and where we are.

41
00:03:35.950 --> 00:03:38.280
When asking someone a question,

42
00:03:38.280 --> 00:03:42.450
don't you think it's polite
to introduce yourself first?

43
00:03:42.450 --> 00:03:45.750
Huh? Oh, yeah, good point.

44
00:03:45.750 --> 00:03:46.910
Sorry about that.

45
00:03:46.910 --> 00:03:49.630
– My name is Crocus.
– I'm Roro... noa...

46
00:03:49.630 --> 00:03:52.840
I'm the lighthouse keeper
of the Twin Capes.

47
00:03:52.840 --> 00:03:54.670
I'm seventy-one and a Gemini.

48
00:03:54.670 --> 00:03:57.340
My blood type is AB.

49
00:03:55.050 --> 00:03:57.340
Let me cut him down!

50
00:03:55.880 --> 00:03:57.340
Hey, calm down.

51
00:03:57.340 --> 00:03:59.510
You want to know where we are?

52
00:04:00.050 --> 00:04:07.600
How dare you barge into my private
resort and run your mouth at me?

53
00:04:08.390 --> 00:04:11.940
Where do you think
we are? A rat's belly?

54
00:04:11.940 --> 00:04:14.780
S-So we were eaten
by the whale after all...

55
00:04:15.490 --> 00:04:18.150
But is this really the inside
of a whale's stomach?

56
00:04:18.150 --> 00:04:21.070
Wait! What's gonna happen to us?!

57
00:04:21.070 --> 00:04:23.120
I don't wanna be digested!

58
00:04:28.460 --> 00:04:30.290
– Cut that out already!
– Cut that out already!

59
00:04:30.290 --> 00:04:33.040
Haven't you kids heard
of the running gag?

60
00:04:33.040 --> 00:04:33.920
– That was a gag?!
– That was a gag?!

61
00:04:33.920 --> 00:04:35.920
The exit is over there.

62
00:04:35.920 --> 00:04:37.420
– We can get out?!
– We can get out?!

63
00:04:38.300 --> 00:04:41.840
Hold on a sec! Why is there
an exit in a whale's stomach?!

64
00:04:41.840 --> 00:04:44.140
And why is the door in the sky?!

65
00:04:44.140 --> 00:04:46.850
Wait... Look at it carefully...

66
00:04:46.850 --> 00:04:51.100
This sky... Those seagulls...

67
00:04:51.770 --> 00:04:53.020
They're all painted!

68
00:04:53.020 --> 00:04:55.400
It's all a painting inside
the whale's stomach!

69
00:04:55.400 --> 00:04:56.610
Huh?!

70
00:04:56.610 --> 00:04:58.240
Call it a doctor's whimsy.

71
00:04:58.240 --> 00:05:00.610
What the hell are you
doing in here, you bastard?!

72
00:05:00.610 --> 00:05:02.320
That's enough. Just ignore him.

73
00:05:02.320 --> 00:05:03.410
Agreed.

74
00:05:03.410 --> 00:05:05.950
Nami! We found the exit,
so let's just get out of here.

75
00:05:05.950 --> 00:05:07.370
Yeah.

76
00:05:12.000 --> 00:05:13.000
What's going on?!

77
00:05:14.840 --> 00:05:16.170
It's started again...

78
00:05:17.300 --> 00:05:18.170
Look at that!

79
00:05:18.970 --> 00:05:20.300
That's not an island!

80
00:05:20.300 --> 00:05:22.590
It's a ship! One that's made of iron!

81
00:05:22.590 --> 00:05:26.100
Oh, of course! It's because
this sea is gastric acid!

82
00:05:26.100 --> 00:05:29.770
Then our wooden ship's gonna
dissolve if we stay here too long.

83
00:05:29.770 --> 00:05:31.980
Hey! What's started?!

84
00:05:31.980 --> 00:05:33.980
Tell us!

85
00:05:34.650 --> 00:05:36.150
It's this whale...

86
00:05:37.650 --> 00:05:42.110
Laboon has started ramming
his head into the Red Line.

87
00:05:51.540 --> 00:05:52.460
– What?!
– What?!

88
00:05:52.460 --> 00:05:56.460
Come to think of it, the whale
had terrible scars on his forehead.

89
00:05:56.460 --> 00:05:58.590
And the way he howled at the sky...

90
00:05:58.590 --> 00:06:00.170
So what?

91
00:06:01.050 --> 00:06:02.630
He's suffering!

92
00:06:09.680 --> 00:06:13.060
Oh, so that's what
the geezer's doing here!

93
00:06:13.060 --> 00:06:13.980
Most likely.

94
00:06:13.980 --> 00:06:17.020
He's probably trying to kill
the whale from the inside!

95
00:06:17.020 --> 00:06:17.860
Now...

96
00:06:17.860 --> 00:06:20.110
What a vicious way to kill it!

97
00:06:20.110 --> 00:06:22.490
Alright, mystery solved.
Now let's go, quick.

98
00:06:22.490 --> 00:06:24.320
We'll be digested if we stay too long.

99
00:06:25.490 --> 00:06:28.330
We have nothing to say
about his whale hunting,

100
00:06:28.330 --> 00:06:30.540
nor do we have any reason
to save the whale.

101
00:06:30.540 --> 00:06:31.830
Let's get out of here.

102
00:06:46.010 --> 00:06:49.470
Dammit! With the waves
surging like this,

103
00:06:49.470 --> 00:06:51.600
I don't know if we can
even reach the doors!

104
00:06:51.600 --> 00:06:53.890
We're gonna have
to paddle! Grab the oars!

105
00:06:53.890 --> 00:06:56.850
Let's speed it up!
I'm worried about Luffy.

106
00:06:56.850 --> 00:06:58.230
He's outside!

107
00:06:58.230 --> 00:07:00.190
I saw him fly out of the mouth!

108
00:07:02.940 --> 00:07:04.950
The old man dove in!

109
00:07:04.950 --> 00:07:05.740
Huh?

110
00:07:06.240 --> 00:07:08.740
What's he doing?
He's gonna be dissolved.

111
00:07:19.130 --> 00:07:21.500
What?! What's going on?!
Huh? Why?!

112
00:07:21.500 --> 00:07:22.760
Dizzy... Dizzy...

113
00:07:22.760 --> 00:07:25.130
I'm getting dizzy!

114
00:07:33.140 --> 00:07:34.390
What now?

115
00:07:34.390 --> 00:07:37.190
Is this the sea? A river? A canal?

116
00:07:47.240 --> 00:07:51.120
Okay. We've infiltrated
this far successfully.

117
00:07:51.160 --> 00:07:53.580
<b>Miss Wednesday
Mysterious Woman</b>

118
00:07:51.830 --> 00:07:53.580
Listen, Miss Wednesday.

119
00:07:53.580 --> 00:07:55.830
The stomach is right
behind these doors,

120
00:07:55.830 --> 00:07:58.460
and that geezer is
most likely there too.

121
00:07:58.460 --> 00:08:01.090
We must eliminate him.

122
00:08:01.130 --> 00:08:03.960
<b>Mr. 9
Mysterious Man</b>

123
00:08:01.710 --> 00:08:03.960
Our goal is the whale.

124
00:08:04.340 --> 00:08:05.970
That's right, Mr. 9.

125
00:08:05.970 --> 00:08:10.430
This whale will be precious,
sweet honey to our town.

126
00:08:13.180 --> 00:08:15.270
Hey! The geezer came back up!

127
00:08:15.270 --> 00:08:16.270
Forget about him.

128
00:08:16.270 --> 00:08:19.770
More importantly, how are
we gonna open those doors?

129
00:08:20.230 --> 00:08:22.770
Okay, Miss Wednesday,

130
00:08:22.770 --> 00:08:25.280
we'll open them on
"Three, two, one, baby!"

131
00:08:25.280 --> 00:08:26.400
Be on your guard.

132
00:08:26.400 --> 00:08:29.360
Roger, Mr. 9.
I'm ready when you are.

133
00:08:31.870 --> 00:08:37.040
I can't stop!

134
00:08:32.990 --> 00:08:34.660
What is this voice, Mr. 9?

135
00:08:34.660 --> 00:08:37.040
I don't know, Miss Wednesday.

136
00:08:47.260 --> 00:08:48.380
Not them again...!

137
00:08:50.930 --> 00:08:52.720
This is bad, Miss Wednesday!

138
00:08:52.720 --> 00:08:55.260
There's a sea of gastric acid below us!

139
00:08:56.850 --> 00:08:57.680
Luffy?

140
00:08:57.680 --> 00:09:00.270
Hey! So everyone's okay?

141
00:09:01.310 --> 00:09:03.690
Anyway... help me!

142
00:09:08.240 --> 00:09:11.950
Two more weirdos
came down with Luffy...

143
00:09:11.950 --> 00:09:14.120
Hey! That old man disappeared!

144
00:09:14.120 --> 00:09:17.160
Forget him. We gotta save Luffy!

145
00:09:31.840 --> 00:09:33.890
Stop it, Laboon.

146
00:09:34.470 --> 00:09:37.470
Don't hurt yourself any more.

147
00:09:37.470 --> 00:09:39.930
There isn't much sedative left...

148
00:09:39.930 --> 00:09:42.390
I'll have to make some more.

149
00:09:44.900 --> 00:09:48.480
That wall divides the world's oceans.

150
00:09:48.480 --> 00:09:53.490
It won't break, even if you hit it
until you die, Laboon.

151
00:09:58.410 --> 00:09:59.790
It's calmed down!

152
00:09:59.790 --> 00:10:01.540
The whale is quiet now.

153
00:10:01.540 --> 00:10:03.420
Seems like it.

154
00:10:03.920 --> 00:10:05.040
Now...

155
00:10:05.960 --> 00:10:09.510
We ended up saving you guys
too, but who are you?

156
00:10:10.340 --> 00:10:13.300
Mr. 9, these people are pirates.

157
00:10:13.300 --> 00:10:15.470
I-I know, Miss Wednesday.

158
00:10:16.180 --> 00:10:20.980
B-But if we explain it to them,
they should understand... perhaps...

159
00:10:20.980 --> 00:10:23.440
You thugs are still at it?

160
00:10:24.150 --> 00:10:26.360
How many times do
I need to tell you?!

161
00:10:26.940 --> 00:10:31.530
You'll never lay a finger on
Laboon as long as I live!

162
00:10:34.110 --> 00:10:35.320
He's back.

163
00:10:35.320 --> 00:10:36.990
Who's that old guy?

164
00:10:38.950 --> 00:10:41.870
No matter what you say,
we can't just leave.

165
00:10:41.870 --> 00:10:44.580
Our mission is to
take down this whale.

166
00:10:44.580 --> 00:10:47.460
You won't interfere with
our whale hunting this time!

167
00:10:47.460 --> 00:10:50.500
We'll blast a hole in his stomach!

168
00:10:50.500 --> 00:10:52.260
Let's go, baby!

169
00:10:51.300 --> 00:10:52.260
Roger!

170
00:10:57.970 --> 00:11:00.100
Those bastards!

171
00:11:04.440 --> 00:11:06.600
The old guy jumped
right into the shots!

172
00:11:06.600 --> 00:11:09.110
Was he... protecting the whale?!

173
00:11:12.530 --> 00:11:14.070
Stop this futile resistance!

174
00:11:14.070 --> 00:11:16.240
Protect this whale all you want!

175
00:11:16.780 --> 00:11:19.990
But this whale will become
food for our town!

176
00:11:26.120 --> 00:11:27.370
What's going on?

177
00:11:35.420 --> 00:11:36.510
Luffy...?

178
00:11:37.220 --> 00:11:38.720
They just...

179
00:11:38.720 --> 00:11:39.970
had it coming.

180
00:11:44.890 --> 00:11:48.650
I thank you for saving me... but why?

181
00:11:48.650 --> 00:11:50.230
I wasn't trying to save you.

182
00:11:50.230 --> 00:11:52.520
I just didn't like them.

183
00:11:53.570 --> 00:11:56.490
Hey, Luffy! What're you doing?
So, who are these guys?

184
00:11:56.490 --> 00:11:59.410
And what are you doing
inside this whale?

185
00:11:57.780 --> 00:11:59.410
Stop it!

186
00:11:59.410 --> 00:12:02.830
Hey! Hey, Luffy! Stop it!
They're thugs from a nearby town.

187
00:12:02.830 --> 00:12:05.080
What are you trying to do?

188
00:12:02.830 --> 00:12:05.620
They're after whale meat.

189
00:12:05.080 --> 00:12:06.830
It belongs to someone else.

190
00:12:05.620 --> 00:12:07.960
If they capture Laboon,

191
00:12:07.960 --> 00:12:11.590
they'd be able to feed their town
for at least two to three years.

192
00:12:11.960 --> 00:12:12.880
Laboon?

193
00:12:12.880 --> 00:12:14.980
That's the name of this whale.

194
00:12:14.980 --> 00:12:20.300
He's an island whale, a species
that only lives in the West Blue.

195
00:12:20.300 --> 00:12:23.060
They're the biggest
whales in the world.

196
00:12:23.060 --> 00:12:26.180
I won't let them use him as food.

197
00:12:26.600 --> 00:12:29.940
There's a reason he keeps hitting
himself against the Red Line

198
00:12:29.940 --> 00:12:35.150
and howling toward Reverse Mountain.

199
00:12:35.150 --> 00:12:35.900
A reason?

200
00:12:35.900 --> 00:12:37.110
Yes.

201
00:12:37.490 --> 00:12:43.030
He's a whale with a human heart.

202
00:12:43.450 --> 00:12:48.460
And he's been devotedly waiting
for a certain pirate crew...

203
00:12:52.130 --> 00:12:54.340
for fifty long years...

204
00:12:54.800 --> 00:12:59.300
This... is Laboon's story...

205
00:13:12.810 --> 00:13:17.480
One day, while I was on duty
as the lighthouse keeper,

206
00:13:17.480 --> 00:13:21.860
some good-natured pirates
came down Reverse Mountain

207
00:13:21.860 --> 00:13:24.530
to enter the Grand Line.

208
00:13:24.530 --> 00:13:29.160
And a small whale came down too,
seemingly following them.

209
00:13:29.160 --> 00:13:31.750
That was Laboon.

210
00:13:32.580 --> 00:13:36.800
As I said before, the island whale
is the largest whale species,

211
00:13:36.800 --> 00:13:38.460
and only lives in the West Blue.

212
00:13:39.470 --> 00:13:43.470
The pirates had been traveling
with Laboon the entire time,

213
00:13:43.470 --> 00:13:50.180
but they left him behind because of
how dangerous the Grand Line is.

214
00:13:50.180 --> 00:13:52.600
But Laboon followed
without them noticing.

215
00:13:53.600 --> 00:13:58.650
Island whales usually travel
with their families in pods,

216
00:13:59.190 --> 00:14:04.110
but I suppose Laboon felt
that the pirates were his family.

217
00:14:04.110 --> 00:14:09.450
Since their ship had broken down,
they stayed here for several months.

218
00:14:09.450 --> 00:14:13.210
We became close friends in that time.

219
00:14:14.830 --> 00:14:17.800
Because of that, on the day
of their departure...

220
00:14:18.420 --> 00:14:20.420
I need to ask you a favor, my friend.

221
00:14:20.420 --> 00:14:23.050
Can you take care of Laboon
for two or three years?

222
00:14:23.590 --> 00:14:27.140
We'll return after sailing
around the world.

223
00:14:28.260 --> 00:14:30.930
Listen up, Laboon.

224
00:14:30.930 --> 00:14:34.520
We're going to enter the Grand Line
and circumnavigate the world.

225
00:14:34.520 --> 00:14:36.940
But please wait for us here.

226
00:14:37.270 --> 00:14:39.190
We're going to a dangerous place.

227
00:14:39.190 --> 00:14:41.530
Too dangerous for you to come along.

228
00:14:42.150 --> 00:14:44.990
Don't worry. Three years
will go by in a flash.

229
00:14:44.990 --> 00:14:46.240
Don't forget...

230
00:14:46.740 --> 00:14:49.490
We'll always be family,
no matter how far apart we are.

231
00:14:53.960 --> 00:14:55.460
Well then, we're setting off.

232
00:14:59.210 --> 00:15:01.300
Guys! We're setting sail!

233
00:15:01.300 --> 00:15:02.840
Hoist the anchor!

234
00:15:02.840 --> 00:15:04.300
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

235
00:15:08.510 --> 00:15:09.760
Laboon!

236
00:15:10.970 --> 00:15:13.060
Wait for us, Laboon!

237
00:15:13.060 --> 00:15:15.520
We promise to return!

238
00:15:15.520 --> 00:15:17.150
Mark my words!

239
00:15:29.700 --> 00:15:32.620
But that was fifty long years ago...

240
00:15:32.620 --> 00:15:33.870
Fifty years?

241
00:15:33.870 --> 00:15:37.250
Laboon's been waiting for those
guys for fifty whole years?

242
00:15:37.250 --> 00:15:41.300
Is that why he continues
to howl and ram into the rocks?

243
00:15:41.300 --> 00:15:42.090
Correct.

244
00:15:51.510 --> 00:15:53.270
This is an amazing canal.

245
00:15:53.270 --> 00:15:56.310
I'm surprised that he's alive
with a hole like this in him.

246
00:15:56.310 --> 00:15:57.940
Was this also your old "whimsy"?

247
00:15:57.940 --> 00:15:59.770
A "doctor's whimsy."

248
00:15:59.770 --> 00:16:00.650
Doctor?

249
00:16:00.650 --> 00:16:02.900
I may not look it,
but yes, I'm a doctor.

250
00:16:02.900 --> 00:16:06.150
I used to run a clinic on
the cape many years ago.

251
00:16:06.150 --> 00:16:08.780
I was also a ship's
doctor for a few years.

252
00:16:08.780 --> 00:16:09.990
Really?

253
00:16:10.490 --> 00:16:12.580
You should be one for our ship!

254
00:16:12.580 --> 00:16:14.370
Don't be ridiculous.

255
00:16:14.370 --> 00:16:18.540
I no longer have the energy to keep
up with you reckless youngsters.

256
00:16:18.540 --> 00:16:21.840
A doctor, huh? That explains why
the whale's insides are like this...

257
00:16:21.840 --> 00:16:23.550
So this is from the treatment?

258
00:16:24.000 --> 00:16:25.550
That's right.

259
00:16:25.550 --> 00:16:31.220
It's impossible to treat a whale
this big from the outside.

260
00:16:31.970 --> 00:16:33.350
I'm opening the doors.

261
00:16:44.270 --> 00:16:46.030
There it is!

262
00:16:46.030 --> 00:16:48.450
The real sky!

263
00:16:57.250 --> 00:16:59.120
Miss Wednesday, what are you...

264
00:17:01.380 --> 00:17:03.540
A whole fifty years, huh?

265
00:17:03.540 --> 00:17:06.000
Those pirates sure are
making him wait...

266
00:17:06.000 --> 00:17:07.260
Idiot.

267
00:17:07.260 --> 00:17:09.340
This is the Grand Line.

268
00:17:09.680 --> 00:17:11.260
They're dead.

269
00:17:13.260 --> 00:17:15.890
They won't come back
no matter how long he waits.

270
00:17:15.890 --> 00:17:20.270
Yeah, because it was basically
uncharted fifty years ago,

271
00:17:20.270 --> 00:17:23.480
the Grand Line was more terrible
and chaotic than it is now.

272
00:17:24.150 --> 00:17:26.730
Why are you being so cynical?!

273
00:17:27.110 --> 00:17:29.030
You don't know that for sure!

274
00:17:29.030 --> 00:17:30.860
They could still come back!

275
00:17:30.860 --> 00:17:32.780
It's such a touching story!

276
00:17:32.780 --> 00:17:35.990
A whale believing in his friends'
promise for fifty long years...

277
00:17:35.990 --> 00:17:37.740
Isn't it, pops?!

278
00:17:38.120 --> 00:17:39.450
Yeah...

279
00:17:39.450 --> 00:17:42.710
But unfortunately, reality is cruel.

280
00:17:42.710 --> 00:17:47.340
I heard from a reliable source...

281
00:17:47.340 --> 00:17:50.420
that they fled the Grand Line.

282
00:17:50.420 --> 00:17:51.970
No way...

283
00:17:51.970 --> 00:17:54.890
You're telling me
they left him behind?!

284
00:17:56.140 --> 00:17:58.220
Fled the Grand Line...

285
00:17:58.220 --> 00:18:00.600
So they crossed
the Calm Belt and lived?

286
00:18:00.600 --> 00:18:03.060
Whether they're alive or not,

287
00:18:03.060 --> 00:18:05.520
I doubt they'll ever return.

288
00:18:05.520 --> 00:18:08.730
Seasons. Weather.
Current. Wind direction.

289
00:18:08.730 --> 00:18:10.990
They're all random here.

290
00:18:10.990 --> 00:18:14.360
Common sense is useless
in the Grand Line.

291
00:18:14.360 --> 00:18:19.200
Weak hearts soon succumb
to fear on the Grand Line.

292
00:18:19.200 --> 00:18:22.830
So the weak of heart
chose to run away,

293
00:18:22.830 --> 00:18:26.710
caring more about their lives
than the promise they made...

294
00:18:28.500 --> 00:18:31.260
They abandoned the whale?!

295
00:18:31.260 --> 00:18:33.880
While he's been waiting
here for fifty years?!

296
00:18:33.880 --> 00:18:35.090
That's too cruel!

297
00:18:35.640 --> 00:18:38.890
If you know that,
why haven't you told him?

298
00:18:39.220 --> 00:18:42.020
He can understand
human speech, right?

299
00:18:42.350 --> 00:18:43.690
I did tell him.

300
00:18:43.690 --> 00:18:46.150
I tried to tell him the whole story.

301
00:18:46.730 --> 00:18:48.940
Laboon! Listen up!

302
00:18:48.940 --> 00:18:51.990
I heard that those pirates
have fled the Grand Line.

303
00:18:52.530 --> 00:18:54.860
I know that you were friends,

304
00:18:55.200 --> 00:18:58.870
and that the promise they made
with you was certainly genuine...

305
00:19:04.960 --> 00:19:06.750
But I'm afraid...

306
00:19:07.330 --> 00:19:09.250
they will never return...

307
00:19:29.520 --> 00:19:32.190
Laboon! Listen to me!

308
00:19:32.190 --> 00:19:33.900
They will never–

309
00:19:42.990 --> 00:19:45.660
I understand that you
don't want to believe it...

310
00:19:46.420 --> 00:19:49.790
but you must accept it somehow!

311
00:19:50.460 --> 00:19:51.170
Laboon!

312
00:19:55.720 --> 00:19:57.260
Laboon!

313
00:20:07.520 --> 00:20:13.360
It was on that day that he began
howling at Reverse Mountain

314
00:20:13.360 --> 00:20:16.990
and ramming his body
against the Red Line...

315
00:20:16.990 --> 00:20:18.910
It's as if he's insisting

316
00:20:18.910 --> 00:20:23.660
they will come down the other side
of that wall any day now...

317
00:20:24.240 --> 00:20:25.540
What a whale...

318
00:20:25.540 --> 00:20:27.710
Even though there's
no point in waiting...

319
00:20:27.710 --> 00:20:31.670
He refuses to believe me because if
I'm right, there would be no reason to wait.

320
00:20:32.340 --> 00:20:36.340
He's afraid of that
more than anything.

321
00:20:36.340 --> 00:20:38.630
His home is in the West Blue...

322
00:20:39.050 --> 00:20:41.010
but there's no way
to return from here.

323
00:20:41.010 --> 00:20:47.140
Those pirates were not only his friends,
but his hope for going home.

324
00:20:47.140 --> 00:20:51.150
While I do feel bad for the whale,

325
00:20:51.150 --> 00:20:53.940
they betrayed you, too, right?

326
00:20:56.280 --> 00:20:58.860
Haven't you taken care
of him long enough?

327
00:20:58.860 --> 00:21:01.530
Look at the scars on his forehead!

328
00:21:01.530 --> 00:21:06.950
If he continues to ram his head
like that, he'll surely die.

329
00:21:06.950 --> 00:21:10.290
It's an odd relationship, but I've
been with him for fifty years.

330
00:21:10.290 --> 00:21:12.330
I can't just stand by
and watch him die.

331
00:21:15.170 --> 00:21:16.800
What's that idiot doing now?

332
00:21:16.800 --> 00:21:18.550
We only looked away for a second...

333
00:21:18.550 --> 00:21:20.510
Does he think he's
a mountain climber?

334
00:21:22.300 --> 00:21:24.930
Gum-Gum...

335
00:21:24.930 --> 00:21:27.020
Bouquet!

336
00:21:27.350 --> 00:21:29.140
Isn't that a mast?

337
00:21:29.140 --> 00:21:31.140
Yep. The one from our ship.

338
00:21:31.140 --> 00:21:32.440
The main mast, yes.

339
00:21:32.770 --> 00:21:35.070
Hey! Don't break the ship!

340
00:21:41.860 --> 00:21:44.320
– What the hell are you doing?!
– What the hell are you doing?!

341
00:21:55.130 --> 00:21:56.210
Wha...?! Hey, kid!

342
00:21:56.590 --> 00:21:59.630
Don't worry! He can't die
from being crushed!

343
00:22:04.430 --> 00:22:05.260
Dummy!

344
00:22:12.020 --> 00:22:13.440
What's he thinking?

345
00:22:17.480 --> 00:22:20.650
Luffy! What the hell
are you trying to do?!

346
00:22:25.490 --> 00:22:26.620
It's a draw!

347
00:22:31.410 --> 00:22:32.710
I'm pretty strong, huh?

348
00:22:34.790 --> 00:22:37.210
Our fight isn't over yet!

349
00:22:37.210 --> 00:22:39.210
We'll have to settle things later!

350
00:22:39.210 --> 00:22:42.800
Your friends might be dead,
but I'll always be your rival!

351
00:22:42.800 --> 00:22:47.010
One day, we definitely gotta
settle this and see who's stronger.

352
00:22:47.010 --> 00:22:50.810
After we go around the Grand Line,
we'll come back to see you again.

353
00:22:52.140 --> 00:22:54.100
When I come back,
we'll finish our fight!

354
00:23:09.700 --> 00:23:10.870
Perfect.

355
00:23:10.870 --> 00:23:14.750
This symbol means
we promise to fight again.

356
00:23:14.750 --> 00:23:20.750
So don't ram into stuff or you'll
erase it before we get back. Got it?!

357
00:23:24.170 --> 00:23:25.930
Alright!

358
00:23:27.800 --> 00:23:28.930
Where'd those guys go?

359
00:23:28.930 --> 00:23:30.390
"Those guys"?

360
00:23:30.390 --> 00:23:32.270
Oh, you mean those two weirdos?

361
00:23:32.270 --> 00:23:33.770
Maybe they ran away?

362
00:23:33.770 --> 00:23:37.060
We never did find out
what their deal was, huh...

363
00:23:39.980 --> 00:23:43.280
Whatever do we do now,
Miss Wednesday?

364
00:23:45.570 --> 00:23:49.320
At the very least, we'll need to
go back and report to the boss...

365
00:23:49.320 --> 00:23:52.080
We were supposed to finish
this mission long ago.

366
00:23:52.080 --> 00:23:56.040
You're right. It would be bad if they
begin to suspect us of treachery.

367
00:23:56.410 --> 00:23:57.170
Indeed.

368
00:23:57.170 --> 00:24:00.500
Since we lost our weapons, we have
to return to base and start over.

369
00:24:00.500 --> 00:24:04.630
If we must. Well then,
let us... begin... Huh?

370
00:24:04.630 --> 00:24:06.970
Um...? Where is...? What?!

371
00:24:07.300 --> 00:24:08.300
What's the matter?

372
00:24:09.840 --> 00:24:10.550
It's gone...

373
00:24:10.550 --> 00:24:11.180
What?

374
00:24:13.930 --> 00:24:14.850
What's this?

375
00:24:15.600 --> 00:24:17.640
You dropped the log pose?!

376
00:24:17.640 --> 00:24:19.350
I apologize, Miss Wednesday!

377
00:24:19.350 --> 00:24:21.650
And we need it to return home...

378
00:24:23.650 --> 00:24:24.780
As it stands–

379
00:24:26.280 --> 00:24:28.660
I-Is that...?!

380
00:24:28.660 --> 00:24:29.360
Huh?

381
00:24:30.950 --> 00:24:32.200
It's...

382
00:24:33.160 --> 00:24:35.120
O-Oh no...

383
00:24:36.040 --> 00:24:37.330
...the Unluckies!

384
00:24:37.330 --> 00:24:38.620
Darn! Are we too late?!

385
00:24:37.750 --> 00:24:41.540
<b>Mr. 13

Mysterious
Sea Otter</b>
<b>Miss Friday

Mysterious
Vulture</b>

386
00:24:38.620 --> 00:24:39.710
Mr. 13!

387
00:24:39.710 --> 00:24:41.540
Miss Friday!

388
00:24:41.880 --> 00:24:44.210
Please wait! We can explain!

389
00:24:44.210 --> 00:24:46.920
We'll report to the boss immediately!

390
00:25:01.060 --> 00:25:05.400
Now then! I finally get to
chart out our Grand Line journey.

391
00:25:10.200 --> 00:25:14.080
Alright! I can finally cook up
the elephant bluefin tuna!

392
00:25:14.080 --> 00:25:15.580
Damn...!

393
00:25:16.540 --> 00:25:20.540
What was Luffy thinking,
wrecking our ship! Really...

394
00:25:20.540 --> 00:25:21.830
Hey, Zoro!

395
00:25:21.830 --> 00:25:24.630
Give me a hand!
I'm not exactly a shipwright!

396
00:25:30.550 --> 00:25:32.140
What's with the screaming?

397
00:25:32.140 --> 00:25:34.010
Is all well, Nami?!

398
00:25:34.010 --> 00:25:36.180
If you're hungry, I have
our meal right here!

399
00:25:36.180 --> 00:25:36.970
Time to eat?

400
00:25:37.310 --> 00:25:39.430
Th-The compass is broken!

401
00:25:40.060 --> 00:25:41.640
It's not pointing anywhere!

402
00:25:41.640 --> 00:25:43.310
Hey, you're right.

403
00:25:43.310 --> 00:25:45.440
It keeps spinning.

404
00:25:45.440 --> 00:25:47.110
Whoa! Neat!

405
00:25:47.980 --> 00:25:51.910
Looks like you guys
came here unprepared.

406
00:25:51.910 --> 00:25:54.990
For heaven's sake!
Did you come here to die?

407
00:25:55.450 --> 00:25:56.080
What?

408
00:25:56.080 --> 00:25:56.790
Food?

409
00:25:56.790 --> 00:25:58.620
You'll be eating hay.

410
00:25:58.620 --> 00:26:00.080
I thought I told you...

411
00:26:00.080 --> 00:26:03.500
Common sense is useless in this sea.

412
00:26:03.500 --> 00:26:06.800
It's not that the compass is broken...

413
00:26:07.590 --> 00:26:09.800
Then, is it the magnetic fields?

414
00:26:09.800 --> 00:26:10.880
Correct.

415
00:26:10.880 --> 00:26:16.260
The islands in the Grand Line
are rich in magnetic minerals.

416
00:26:16.260 --> 00:26:19.020
They cause abnormalities
throughout the Grand Line.

417
00:26:19.020 --> 00:26:22.440
Furthermore, the current and wind
patterns are never consistent.

418
00:26:22.440 --> 00:26:26.270
As a navigator, you should know
how terrifying that is.

419
00:26:26.270 --> 00:26:30.490
We'll have no hope of survival without
a way to know our direction...

420
00:26:30.490 --> 00:26:31.440
Yummy!

421
00:26:31.440 --> 00:26:33.570
I-I didn't know! Oh, well...

422
00:26:33.570 --> 00:26:36.200
Hey! That's really bad!
Are we gonna be okay?!

423
00:26:36.200 --> 00:26:38.660
This isn't bad. It's yummy!

424
00:26:38.660 --> 00:26:41.620
Can you guys be quiet
for one second?!

425
00:26:41.620 --> 00:26:44.790
The nose of the elephant
bluefin tuna tastes good!

426
00:26:45.250 --> 00:26:50.260
You need a log pose to travel
around the Grand Line.

427
00:26:50.260 --> 00:26:52.510
Log pose? I've never heard of it.

428
00:26:52.510 --> 00:26:56.510
It's a special compass
that can record magnetism.

429
00:26:56.510 --> 00:26:58.050
Like a weird-looking compass?

430
00:26:58.050 --> 00:27:00.640
Yes, its shape is quite unusual.

431
00:27:00.640 --> 00:27:02.060
Something like this?

432
00:27:02.060 --> 00:27:03.180
Yeah, that's the one.

433
00:27:03.640 --> 00:27:08.570
It's impossible to navigate
the Grand Line without a log pose.

434
00:27:09.320 --> 00:27:10.820
I see.

435
00:27:10.820 --> 00:27:12.570
But hold on a second...

436
00:27:13.070 --> 00:27:14.490
Luffy?

437
00:27:14.860 --> 00:27:17.490
How come you have one?!

438
00:27:19.200 --> 00:27:23.290
Those two weirdos
dropped it on the ship.

439
00:27:23.290 --> 00:27:24.460
They did?

440
00:27:24.460 --> 00:27:25.830
Why'd you hit me?

441
00:27:25.830 --> 00:27:26.790
It felt right.

442
00:27:26.790 --> 00:27:27.750
Fair enough.

443
00:27:29.000 --> 00:27:30.340
So this is a log pose.

444
00:27:30.340 --> 00:27:31.880
There's no dial face.

445
00:27:31.880 --> 00:27:39.470
The magnetic fields of islands in
the Grand Line follow a certain rule:

446
00:27:39.470 --> 00:27:44.640
By recording the magnetism of
two islands pulling against each other,

447
00:27:44.640 --> 00:27:47.150
you can find the route
to the next island.

448
00:27:47.650 --> 00:27:50.820
Since you can't even figure out
your location in this sea,

449
00:27:50.820 --> 00:27:54.650
the magnetic record of the log pose
is the only thing you can depend on.

450
00:27:55.110 --> 00:28:01.780
To begin, you must pick one of
Reverse Mountain's seven magnetic fields.

451
00:28:01.780 --> 00:28:04.700
But no matter which route you take,

452
00:28:04.700 --> 00:28:08.580
the magnetic pulls will eventually
push you onto one route.

453
00:28:08.580 --> 00:28:12.130
And the name of the island
at the end of the voyage is...

454
00:28:12.630 --> 00:28:13.960
Laugh Tale.

455
00:28:13.960 --> 00:28:16.760
It's the last island in the Grand Line.

456
00:28:16.760 --> 00:28:20.970
The only one in history to confirm
its existence is the King of the Pirates.

457
00:28:20.970 --> 00:28:23.100
It's a legendary island.

458
00:28:23.100 --> 00:28:24.470
Laugh Tale...

459
00:28:24.470 --> 00:28:27.310
So is that where the One Piece is?!

460
00:28:27.310 --> 00:28:30.360
Who knows. That's the most
prominent theory,

461
00:28:30.360 --> 00:28:33.070
but no one else has
been able to get there.

462
00:28:33.070 --> 00:28:34.690
Then...

463
00:28:34.690 --> 00:28:36.240
we'll be the first to prove it.

464
00:28:39.110 --> 00:28:41.820
Alright, I'm done!
You guys wanna get going?

465
00:28:41.820 --> 00:28:43.660
You ate the whole thing?!

466
00:28:43.660 --> 00:28:45.330
Whoa! Even the bones are gone.

467
00:28:45.330 --> 00:28:48.620
A log pose, huh? We'd better
take good care of this.

468
00:28:48.620 --> 00:28:50.830
This is the key to
the rest of our journey.

469
00:28:50.830 --> 00:28:52.590
You damn rubber man!

470
00:28:52.590 --> 00:28:55.210
I made Nami such 
a delicious meal and she...

471
00:28:56.010 --> 00:28:59.130
she didn't even have a bite!

472
00:29:14.020 --> 00:29:14.980
What was that for?

473
00:29:14.980 --> 00:29:17.400
Take that, you damn rubber man.

474
00:29:16.320 --> 00:29:17.400
Sanji...

475
00:29:17.400 --> 00:29:18.860
Yes, Nami!

476
00:29:19.700 --> 00:29:22.820
You two should go
cool your heads off!

477
00:29:27.200 --> 00:29:29.210
Hey, hold on a sec...

478
00:29:29.660 --> 00:29:32.960
Wasn't that thing
super-duper important?!

479
00:29:32.960 --> 00:29:35.460
Our precious log pose...

480
00:29:35.460 --> 00:29:37.800
Don't panic. You can have mine.

481
00:29:38.210 --> 00:29:40.720
Think of it as thanks
for helping Laboon.

482
00:29:48.220 --> 00:29:50.230
Man... I thought I was a goner. Huh?

483
00:29:52.850 --> 00:29:55.980
Here, take my hand, dear lady.

484
00:29:55.980 --> 00:29:57.030
Oh, thank you.

485
00:29:57.030 --> 00:29:58.230
Nice day, isn't it?

486
00:29:58.230 --> 00:29:59.030
Hey!

487
00:29:59.650 --> 00:30:00.950
We must ask you a favor.

488
00:30:04.570 --> 00:30:05.870
Whisky Peak?

489
00:30:06.200 --> 00:30:07.410
That's a weird name.

490
00:30:07.410 --> 00:30:08.490
What's that?

491
00:30:08.490 --> 00:30:11.250
That's where we live... um, sir.

492
00:30:11.250 --> 00:30:13.370
What happened to your ship?

493
00:30:13.370 --> 00:30:15.840
I'm afraid it was destroyed.

494
00:30:16.460 --> 00:30:20.550
That's a pretty big favor for someone
who just tried to kill the whale, Mr. 9.

495
00:30:20.970 --> 00:30:22.880
So who are you guys, anyway?

496
00:30:22.880 --> 00:30:24.590
I'm a king.

497
00:30:25.680 --> 00:30:26.640
Liar.

498
00:30:27.890 --> 00:30:29.640
We can't say!

499
00:30:29.640 --> 00:30:31.890
We just want to go back home.

500
00:30:31.890 --> 00:30:35.230
We don't like being
secretive either, but...

501
00:30:35.230 --> 00:30:37.650
...our company motto is "Mystery."

502
00:30:37.650 --> 00:30:40.070
We simply can't tell you
anything about us.

503
00:30:40.400 --> 00:30:43.780
Trusting your good
character, we beg of you!

504
00:30:43.780 --> 00:30:46.160
I assure you, we will return the favor.

505
00:30:46.160 --> 00:30:47.990
Don't do it.

506
00:30:47.990 --> 00:30:51.080
No matter what they say,
they're dishonest people.

507
00:30:51.500 --> 00:30:56.580
By the way, we broke the log pose.
Do you still want a ride?

508
00:30:56.920 --> 00:31:00.130
What?! You broke it?!
That was mine, you know!

509
00:31:00.130 --> 00:31:04.180
You dare act smug while we're being
humble?! You're all stuck here as well!

510
00:31:04.550 --> 00:31:05.970
Oh, I forgot to mention...

511
00:31:05.970 --> 00:31:09.140
We do have a spare,
courtesy of Mr. Crocus.

512
00:31:09.970 --> 00:31:12.140
We beg you people
of such character...

513
00:31:12.520 --> 00:31:15.100
Dammit! This minx is toying with us!

514
00:31:15.440 --> 00:31:16.940
Sure, you can ride with us.

515
00:31:18.360 --> 00:31:19.820
Whisky Peak, right?

516
00:31:19.820 --> 00:31:20.980
Let's go there.

517
00:31:20.980 --> 00:31:21.730
– What?
– Huh?

518
00:31:21.730 --> 00:31:25.950
Hey, are you sure we wanna go out of
our way to take these shady guys?

519
00:31:26.320 --> 00:31:27.370
What's the problem?

520
00:31:27.370 --> 00:31:29.410
Don't sweat the small stuff.

521
00:31:29.410 --> 00:31:34.370
Once you choose your route here,
you won't be able to change it.

522
00:31:34.370 --> 00:31:37.210
If we don't like it,
we'll just go around again.

523
00:31:37.750 --> 00:31:39.130
Is that so...?

524
00:31:39.670 --> 00:31:41.500
So, should we get going?

525
00:31:42.880 --> 00:31:45.970
Since I've made my promise
with the whale, let's sail out.

526
00:31:46.340 --> 00:31:48.720
Who in the world are you?

527
00:31:48.720 --> 00:31:49.680
Me?

528
00:31:49.680 --> 00:31:50.560
I'm...

529
00:31:50.970 --> 00:31:53.140
the man who's gonna be
King of the Pirates!

530
00:31:57.600 --> 00:31:59.190
What a foolish pirate...

531
00:32:02.070 --> 00:32:03.610
You should be good to go.

532
00:32:03.610 --> 00:32:05.650
The log must have
been stored by now.

533
00:32:06.280 --> 00:32:08.740
Is it pointing at the same
direction as the map?

534
00:32:08.740 --> 00:32:09.490
Yep.

535
00:32:10.200 --> 00:32:12.160
It's pointing at Whisky Peak.

536
00:32:12.660 --> 00:32:14.500
See ya, flower guy!

537
00:32:14.500 --> 00:32:16.080
Thanks for the log pose!

538
00:32:16.080 --> 00:32:18.000
Yeah. Have a safe trip!

539
00:32:18.000 --> 00:32:20.630
See ya, too, whale! I'm leaving now!

540
00:32:25.590 --> 00:32:27.550
Full speed ahead...

541
00:32:27.550 --> 00:32:29.930
to Whisky Peak!

542
00:32:29.930 --> 00:32:31.930
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

543
00:32:49.570 --> 00:32:54.450
Could they be the pirates we've been
waiting for all this time...?

544
00:32:54.450 --> 00:32:58.410
That man has a particularly
strange air about him...

545
00:33:01.460 --> 00:33:02.670
don't you think,

546
00:33:02.670 --> 00:33:04.380
Roger?
